title: 192nd Wing - Virginia Air National Guard
og_description: Explore highlights of the various Air Force Specialty Codes in the 192nd Wing, Virginia Air National Guard. With more than 1,200 Airmen currently serving in approximately 145 AFSCs, the mission of the 192nd Wing is to provide a fully-trained organization of volunteer-Airmen dedicated to protect and defend the vital interests of the nation, state and community. The wing is headquartered at Joint Base Langley-Eustis, Virginia. In addition to state missions, the wing associates with the regular Air Force, spanning three major commands, and performs standalone federal missions. (U.S. Air National Guard video by Staff Sgt. Danielle Lofton)

og_description: Exercises Clean Care and Vigorous Warrior 2024 combined chemical, biological, radiological, and nuclear defense with military medical care this year to train 1,600 soldiers from 35 NATO ally and partner nations April 28 to May 9 at the Bakony Combat Training Center in Hungary. og_title: MRF-D 24.3: U.S. Marines, ADF, UK Armed Forces participate in Exercise Predator’s Run 24
og_description: U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force –Darwin 24.3, Australian Defence Force service members, and British Royal Marine Commandos, participate in Exercise Predator’s Run 24 at Mount Bundey Training Area, NT, Australia, July 16 to Aug. 7, 2024. Exercise Predator’s Run 24 is a littoral-focused, multilateral training exercise led by the Australian Army’s 1st Brigade. MRF-D 24.3 is integrated into the Australian Defence Force order of battle, conducting warfighting and live-fire field evolutions, with a focus on executing and integrating offensive, defensive, and counterattack maneuvers, emphasizing combined arms in support of maneuver. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Juan Torres)  This video contains music from USMC enterprise licensed assets from Adobe Stock: Come 2gether by Ooyy, Standoff by Nylonia, Transmission Road by Nylonia and Solitary Morning by Nylonia.
